## COMPOSITION CHECKLIST

Before finalizing any screen, evaluate against these questions:

### Hierarchy & Emphasis
- [ ] Can I name the #1 element on this screen within 1 second?
- [ ] Is there a clear primary → secondary → tertiary visual order?
- [ ] Is the primary CTA the most emphasized interactive element?

### Balance & Proportion
- [ ] Does the layout feel stable (symmetrical) or intentionally dynamic (asymmetrical)?
- [ ] Are element sizes proportional to their importance?
- [ ] Do icons, text, and containers maintain harmonious proportions?

### Contrast & Color
- [ ] Does text meet WCAG contrast minimums (4.5:1 / 3:1)?
- [ ] Is there exactly ONE accent color used for primary actions?
- [ ] Are non-neutral colors limited to 2 (accent + status)?

### Unity & Variety
- [ ] Do all elements feel like they belong to the same visual system?
- [ ] Is there enough variation to prevent monotony and aid scanning?
- [ ] Are border-radius, shadows, and spacing consistent across components?

### Rhythm & Movement
- [ ] Does spacing follow a predictable pattern (e.g., 16/24/48)?
- [ ] Does the eye naturally flow from primary to CTA?
- [ ] Do scan patterns (F or Z) align with content placement?

### White Space, Lines & Texture
- [ ] Is there breathing room between sections (30-40% visible background)?
- [ ] Am I using alignment (implied lines) instead of explicit dividers where possible?
- [ ] Does texture enhance or compete with content?

### Shapes & Pattern
- [ ] Is the shape language consistent (same radius, same style)?
- [ ] Do UI patterns follow platform conventions?
- [ ] Are all circular elements truly circular (width = height)?

